            "content": "\n# Odin\n\nThis website aims to provide insights about ETNA's infrastucture, such as availability or the response time.\n\n## Tools\n\n[isetnadown.com](https://isetnadown.com) leverages the following open-source solutions:\n- [Grafana](https://grafana.com/)\n- [Prometheus](prometheus.io/)\n- [Docker](https://www.docker.com/)\n- [Odin](https://github.com/tbobm/odin)\n\n## Contributing\n\nIf you have any idea or recommendation, please feel free to create an issue in [odin](https://github.com/tbobm/odin/issues/new).\n\n## Charts\n\nEvery visualisation _should_ have a matching tooltip explaining the purpose of the chart and a brief description of the data gathering process.\nYou can read those informations by hovering over the little _i_ on the top-left corner of the chart.\n\n### Target unreachability\n\nEvery N second, try to reach the **target** by performing an HTTP call using the corresponding **method**.\n\n- If the server takes longer than X seconds to start answering, we consider it as \"unreachable\" (**1**). This metric does not take the response duration in account, only *the time the server takes to start sending back some bytes*.\n- If the server takes less than X seconds to answer, we consider it as \"reachable\" (**0**)\n\n\n",
